# Auto-push to GitHub

After completing any user-requested code change in this project:

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review changes.
2. Stage all relevant files. Never commit `.env`, secrets, or credentials.
3. Create a concise commit message focused on why the change was made.
4. Push to `origin/main` with `git push origin main`.
5. Confirm the push succeeded and share the commit hash with the user.

Skip auto-push only when:
- The user explicitly says not to push
- There are no file changes to commit
- Push fails (report the error and do not force-push)
